      "content": "I'm glad you're trying to keep things simple. The \"creaky door\" analogy is just a way to describe the sound of the brake rotors vibrating and producing a high-pitched noise, similar to the sound of a creaky door that's out of alignment. It's not a perfect comparison, but it gives you an idea of what's happening.\n\nAs for the cost, it's possible that it's a simple fix, but it's also possible that it's a more significant issue. If the rotors are warped or uneven, it may be more cost-effective to replace them rather than trying to repair them. However, if it's just a matter of dirty brake pads or a loose caliper, a simple cleaning or adjustment might do the trick. It's always best to have a professional mechanic take a look to determine the cause and recommend the best course of action.",
